the ex trials events at stanford the ex trials facebook twitter email print add to calendar short event description the ex trials is an original one act comedy written by savannah kopp and directed by laura petree when couples break up you have to choose sides but what if you re all friends fed up with the strife jack and erika's break up has caused their friend group rebecca andy and allie take the most reasonable course of action they put jack and erika up on trial to decide once and for all who was right the ex trials is a tale of custody arrangements for a stuffed elephant tapped phone lines sabotage and truth and all the little things that people do to drive us crazy when friday mar 2 2012 7 00 pm saturday mar 3 2012 2 00 pm saturday mar 3 2012 7 00 pm approximate duration of 2.0 hour s where roble hall theater map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends tags arts performance drama sponsor stanford institute for creativity and the arts contact 650 736 4087 sica stanford edu admission free permalink http events stanford edu events 312 31243 last modified february 23 2012
